00:02:04.570 --> 00:02:07.840
Now in reality,
most markets fall

00:02:07.840 --> 00:02:11.460
between perfect competition,
which never truly exists,

00:02:11.460 --> 00:02:13.720
and monopoly, which
rarely exists.

00:02:13.720 --> 00:02:17.200
Most markets are in between,
we call them oligopolies.

00:02:17.200 --> 00:02:20.830
That's markets
with several firms

00:02:20.830 --> 00:02:22.750
but not perfectly competing.

00:02:22.750 --> 00:02:24.035
And we'll get to that.

00:02:24.035 --> 00:02:26.410
But that's actually one of
the harder things we'll cover,

00:02:26.410 --> 00:02:28.780
